"{\"uid\": \"ms.now-opinion-msnbc-opinion-paris-olympics-womens-ruby-ilona-maher-tiktok-bmi-rcna164574\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Opinion  Morning Joe  RacheL Maddow  Deadline: White House  The weekend  NEWSLETTERS  Share this -  Opinion  One of Team USA's rugby stars went viral for a TikTok educating her haters.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 184, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 47, \"end\": 58, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/White_House\", \"score\": 0.9987678605813467, \"rank\": 0.0012291514022865796, \"text\": \"White House\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/White_House\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/White_House\"}, {\"begin\": 116, \"end\": 124, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.996831587897093, \"rank\": 0.003055796853529156, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 156, \"end\": 162, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TikTok\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.507009988511289e-42, \"text\": \"TikTok\", \"types\": [\"Q7397\", \"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TikTok\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TikTok\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And it highlights one of the best parts about the Olympic Games.\", \"from\": 185, \"to\": 249, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Ilona Maheris having herself atimeat the Paris Olympics.\", \"from\": 251, \"to\": 307, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 251, \"end\": 256, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ilona_Mitrecey\", \"score\": 0.9996565302920677, \"rank\": 0.0003435859629849742, \"text\": \"Ilona\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ilona_Mitrecey\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ilona_Mitrecey\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 27-year-old rugby player just captured a bronze medal after Team USA'simprobable winin the finals seconds of Tuesday night's match against Australia - the first medal ever for American women's rugby sevens.\", \"from\": 308, \"to\": 518, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 451, \"end\": 460, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.9985232723543672, \"rank\": 0.0014256595736154229, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}, {\"begin\": 488, \"end\": 496, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9983434301935044, \"rank\": 0.0016439695098079666, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But even before the win, Maher had become a burgeoning social media sensation.\", \"from\": 519, \"to\": 597, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Footage of her stiff-arming opponents hasdrawn comparisonsto Baltimore Ravens star Derrick Henry, and her impressiveTikTok accounthas gone viral with videos highlighting an endearingly quirky and honest personality.\", \"from\": 598, \"to\": 813, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 659, \"end\": 675, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Baltimore_Ravens\", \"score\": 0.9999999978176675, \"rank\": 2.157096911459658e-09, \"text\": \"Baltimore Ravens\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Baltimore_Ravens\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Baltimore_Ravens\"}, {\"begin\": 681, \"end\": 694, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Derrick_Henry\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Derrick Henry\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q14128148\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Derrick_Henry\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Derrick_Henry\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A consistent theme in Maher's social media posts is her advocacy for body positivity, which is touted on her official Team USA profile.\", \"from\": 815, \"to\": 950, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 933, \"end\": 941, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.996831587897093, \"rank\": 0.003055796853529156, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A consistent theme in Maher's social media posts is her advocacy for body positivity, which is touted on her officialTeam USA profile.\", \"from\": 952, \"to\": 1086, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Last week, she posted a reelon Instagramstating that \\\"all body types can be Olympians.\\\"\", \"from\": 1087, \"to\": 1174, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"As the Olympics officially start today, I want you all to take a look at all the different body types on display,\\\" she said.\", \"from\": 1176, \"to\": 1301, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"All body types matter, all body types are worthy, from the smallest gymnast to the tallest volleyball player, from a rugby player to a shot-putter to a sprinter.\", \"from\": 1302, \"to\": 1464, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"All body types are beautiful and can do amazing things, so truly see yourself in these athletes and know that you can do it, too.\\\"\", \"from\": 1465, \"to\": 1595, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The reaction to Maher's posts has been overwhelmingly positive, but she's unsurprisingly had to deal with a few trolls commenting on her weight and Body Mass Index (BMI).\", \"from\": 1597, \"to\": 1767, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1745, \"end\": 1766, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Body_mass_index\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Body Mass Index (BMI)\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Body_mass_index\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Body_mass_index\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"One person in particular wrote, \\\"I bet that person has a 30 percent BMI,\\\" prompting Maher to respond directly with a candid message about her body.\", \"from\": 1768, \"to\": 1915, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1836, \"end\": 1839, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Body_mass_index\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.343634939355622e-33, \"text\": \"BMI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Body_mass_index\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Body_mass_index\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I think you were trying to roast me, but this actually is a fact.\", \"from\": 1916, \"to\": 1982, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I do have a BMI of 30 - well, 29.3 to be more exact,\\\" sheshared on TikTok.\", \"from\": 1983, \"to\": 2057, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1995, \"end\": 1998, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Body_mass_index\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.343634939355622e-33, \"text\": \"BMI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Body_mass_index\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Body_mass_index\"}, {\"begin\": 2050, \"end\": 2056, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TikTok\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.507009988511289e-42, \"text\": \"TikTok\", \"types\": [\"Q7397\", \"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TikTok\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TikTok\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Maher noted that misperceptions about weight and athleticism are nothing new; in middle school, she received a physical that labeled her overweight.\", \"from\": 2058, \"to\": 2206, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Today, Maher is one of the best women's rugby players in the world.\", \"from\": 2208, \"to\": 2275, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The notion that her body is in anything but optimal shape is absurd.\", \"from\": 2276, \"to\": 2344, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"As long as haters keep saying dumb stuff, I am gonna keep clapping back  BMI is also a famouslyflawed and inaccurate measure of health, a fact that rings even truer for athletes.\", \"from\": 2346, \"to\": 2524, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2419, \"end\": 2422, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Body_mass_index\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.343634939355622e-33, \"text\": \"BMI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Body_mass_index\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Body_mass_index\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This simple calculation uses weight and height to measure body fat, but does not account for important factors like bone density and muscle mass.\", \"from\": 2525, \"to\": 2670, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"As a world-class professional, Maher has access to dietitians and medical experts, whom she says have told her\\u00a0it's not a particularly useful measurement for athletes.\", \"from\": 2671, \"to\": 2838, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In her TikTok post, Maher reiterates that she's 5-foot-10 and 200 pounds - 170 of which is lean muscle.\", \"from\": 2839, \"to\": 2942, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2846, \"end\": 2852, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TikTok\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.507009988511289e-42, \"text\": \"TikTok\", \"types\": [\"Q7397\", \"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TikTok\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TikTok\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That gives her a body fat percentage of 15% - well below the25-31% rangeconsidered healthy for average women who are not athletes.More from MS NOW DailyMust reads from Today's listMissouri's failed DEI suit vs. Starbucks offers lessons to Big BusinessJa'han JonesByron Donalds faces racist attacks in Florida's ugly GOP gubernatorial primaryJa'han JonesMaher certainly does not need me, or anyone else, to defend her body to random people on the internet (who, as she points out, did not just win a bronze medal in the Olympics).\", \"from\": 2943, \"to\": 3472, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3154, \"end\": 3163, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Starbucks\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Starbucks\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Starbucks\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Starbucks\"}, {\"begin\": 3212, \"end\": 3219, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lists_of_mountains_and_hills_in_the_British_Isles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.1348822489527535e-18, \"text\": \"Donalds\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lists_of_mountains_and_hills_in_the_British_Isles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lists_of_mountains_and_hills_in_the_British_Isles\"}, {\"begin\": 3244, \"end\": 3251, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Florida\", \"score\": 0.9995629710913916, \"rank\": 0.000388704758110786, \"text\": \"Florida\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Florida\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Florida\"}, {\"begin\": 3259, \"end\": 3262, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republican_Party_of_Texas\", \"score\": 0.9995011567364411, \"rank\": 0.00033747460631664917, \"text\": \"GOP\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republican_Party_of_Texas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republican_Party_of_Texas\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But if anything, the Games offer a rare opportunity to witness and celebrate a trulydiverse range of body types, particularly among women.\", \"from\": 3473, \"to\": 3611, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Gymnasts are not built the same as rugby players; weightlifters look dramatically different than swimmers.MultipleOlympiansacross the various sports have talked about body image and how harmful the narrow view of what constitutes healthy bodies can be, especially for young girls.Gymnasts are not built the same as rugby players; weightlifters look dramatically different than swimmers.Much of this conversation in recent years has centered around notions of what \\\"feminine\\\" bodies are supposed to look like; some female athleteshave admittedthat they avoid building muscle because they believe that looking overly bulky hurts their marketability.But it should be noted that these conversations are by no means limited to women in sports.\", \"from\": 3612, \"to\": 4350, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"For years, ESPN the Magazine's \\\"The Body Issue\\\" celebrated diversity in body types for men and women athletes alike.\", \"from\": 4351, \"to\": 4467, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4362, \"end\": 4366, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/ESPN\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.840812165402898e-20, \"text\": \"ESPN\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/ESPN\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/ESPN\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"When Texas Rangers first baseman Prince Fielderappeared on the coverin 2014, his husky build stood in sharpcontrast toother players who would be considered more traditionally fit.\", \"from\": 4468, \"to\": 4647, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4473, \"end\": 4486, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Texas_Ranger_Division\", \"score\": 0.998504567698325, \"rank\": 0.001488656601098279, \"text\": \"Texas Rangers\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Texas_Ranger_Division\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Texas_Ranger_Division\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But Fielder deserved to be on that cover: A six-time All-Star, he was among the game's most feared power hitters in his prime.Thankfully, notions of what a healthy body looks like are changing, even as Maher's comment section proves they certainly still exist.\", \"from\": 4648, \"to\": 4908, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Events like the Olympics are the perfect time to call out and celebrate the athletes and body types that we do not often get to see on an international stage.\", \"from\": 4909, \"to\": 5067, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"For her part, Maher just used her\\\"big, broad, beautiful shoulders\\\"to stiff-arm her way to the Olympic podium.\", \"from\": 5068, \"to\": 5177, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Must reads from Today's list  Maher certainly does not need me, or anyone else, to defend her body to random people on the internet (who, as she points out, did not just win a bronze medal in the Olympics).\", \"from\": 5179, \"to\": 5385, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But if anything, the Games offer a rare opportunity to witness and celebrate a trulydiverse range of body types, particularly among women.\", \"from\": 5386, \"to\": 5524, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Gymnasts are not built the same as rugby players; weightlifters look dramatically different than swimmers.MultipleOlympiansacross the various sports have talked about body image and how harmful the narrow view of what constitutes healthy bodies can be, especially for young girls.\", \"from\": 5525, \"to\": 5805, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Gymnasts are not built the same as rugby players; weightlifters look dramatically different than swimmers.\", \"from\": 5807, \"to\": 5913, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Much of this conversation in recent years has centered around notions of what \\\"feminine\\\" bodies are supposed to look like; some female athleteshave admittedthat they avoid building muscle because they believe that looking overly bulky hurts their marketability.\", \"from\": 5915, \"to\": 6176, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But it should be noted that these conversations are by no means limited to women in sports.\", \"from\": 6178, \"to\": 6269, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"For years, ESPN the Magazine's \\\"The Body Issue\\\" celebrated diversity in body types for men and women athletes alike.\", \"from\": 6270, \"to\": 6386, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6281, \"end\": 6285, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/ESPN\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.840812165402898e-20, \"text\": \"ESPN\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/ESPN\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/ESPN\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"When Texas Rangers first baseman Prince Fielderappeared on the coverin 2014, his husky build stood in sharpcontrast toother players who would be considered more traditionally fit.\", \"from\": 6387, \"to\": 6566, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6392, \"end\": 6405, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Texas_Ranger_Division\", \"score\": 0.998504567698325, \"rank\": 0.001488656601098279, \"text\": \"Texas Rangers\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Texas_Ranger_Division\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Texas_Ranger_Division\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But Fielder deserved to be on that cover: A six-time All-Star, he was among the game's most feared power hitters in his prime.\", \"from\": 6567, \"to\": 6693, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Thankfully, notions of what a healthy body looks like are changing, even as Maher's comment section proves they certainly still exist.\", \"from\": 6695, \"to\": 6829, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Events like the Olympics are the perfect time to call out and celebrate the athletes and body types that we do not often get to see on an international stage.\", \"from\": 6830, \"to\": 6988, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"For her part, Maher just used her\\\"big, broad, beautiful shoulders\\\"to stiff-arm her way to the Olympic podium.\", \"from\": 6989, \"to\": 7098, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Kavitha A. Davidson    Kavitha A. Davidson is an Emmy-winning sports journalist from New York.\", \"from\": 7100, \"to\": 7194, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7100, \"end\": 7107, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/K._Kavitha\", \"score\": 0.9797051839231586, \"rank\": 0.02071522778708922, \"text\": \"Kavitha\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/K._Kavitha\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/K._Kavitha\"}, {\"begin\": 7111, \"end\": 7119, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Davidson_College\", \"score\": 0.9999648968441236, \"rank\": 3.510436378173233e-05, \"text\": \"Davidson\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Davidson_College\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Davidson_College\"}, {\"begin\": 7123, \"end\": 7130, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/K._Kavitha\", \"score\": 0.9795725843398844, \"rank\": 0.02071522778708922, \"text\": \"Kavitha\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/K._Kavitha\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/K._Kavitha\"}, {\"begin\": 7134, \"end\": 7142, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Davidson_College\", \"score\": 0.9999648968441236, \"rank\": 3.510436378173233e-05, \"text\": \"Davidson\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Davidson_College\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Davidson_College\"}, {\"begin\": 7185, \"end\": 7193, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"score\": 0.9999999992301127, \"rank\": 5.788146855416676e-10, \"text\": \"New York\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She was most recently a correspondent on HBO's \\\"Real Sports with Bryant Gumbel.\\\"\", \"from\": 7195, \"to\": 7275, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7236, \"end\": 7239, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/HBO\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0730966590566358e-14, \"text\": \"HBO\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/HBO\", \"dbpedia\": \"